Metric 1 name: Requests Each User Can Make Per Hour
Metric 1 description: The API limits the number of requests per hour that a user can do to protect the API of abuse and codes full of "buggycodes" errors. Each account has a point deposit "Tokens" of requests, with 4500 tokens initially. 75 tokens are added every minute until it is coming back to the maximum of 4500. If many requests are made and said deposit is emptied, the error code 429 is returned, since we have done so many requests once we have emptied the deposit . On the other hand we can know how many tokens we are looking at the Endpoint Rate Limit (requests to this do not compute to remove tokens)
Metric 2 description: The API limits the number of elements that are returned in a list, in such a way that a response from the API which is a list will be by default 200 elements and 1000 at most. If more than those 1000 items we will receive a status code 206 indicating that the return list is a partial list (part of a larger list) and that to access the other data of that list we must make use of the Parameters that are mentioned ... (Order, Max and Range)
